
[1]marine

   MARINE, a. [L. marinus, from mare,the sea.]

   1. Pertaining to the sea; as marine productions or bodies; marine
   shells.

   2. Transacted at sea; done on the ocean; as a marine engagement.

   3. Doing duty on the sea; as a marine officer; marine forces.

        MARINE, n. A soldier that serves on board of a ship in naval
     engagements. In the plural, marines, a body of troops trained to do
                     military service on board of ships.

   1. The whole navy of a kingdom or state.

   2. The whole economy of naval affairs, comprehending the building,
   rigging, equipping,navigating and management of ships of war in
   engagements.
